{"id":27,"date":"2020-07-09T20:45:00","date_gmt":"2020-07-09T20:45:00","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/localhost:8000\/?p=27"},"modified":"2021-02-02T07:05:29","modified_gmt":"2021-02-02T07:05:29","slug":"micronaut-2-0-rest-api-swagger-ui-with-maven-and-kotlin","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"http:\/\/localhost:8000\/2020\/07\/09\/micronaut-2-0-rest-api-swagger-ui-with-maven-and-kotlin\/","title":{"rendered":"Micronaut 2.0 REST API Swagger UI with Maven and Kotlin"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>I was playing around with Micronaut framework 2.0 which was released a couple of days ago (June 26th) for a personal project, a web service with a REST API. I wanted to use Swagger UI, but Micronaut\u2019s documentation does not cover how to set it up with Maven and Kotlin. It went something like this.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https:\/\/micronaut.io\/launch\/\">Generate<\/a> a new Micronaut 2.0 project.<\/li><li>Add some REST endpoints.<\/li><li>Follow the Micronaut <a href=\"https:\/\/micronaut-projects.github.io\/micronaut-openapi\/1.5.1\/guide\/index.html\">OpenAPI\/Swagger docs<\/a> (1.5.1).<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Run the server, and the OpenAPI definition file should be available at: <a href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/swagger-ui\">http:\/\/localhost:8080\/swagger-ui<\/a>. But it&#8217;s not.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The documentation only works for Maven and Java, but does not work with Kotlin (due to kapt).<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The solution is rather simple. We need to add the following line to <code>&lt;annotationProcessorArgs&gt;<\/code> of the <code>kotlin-maven-plugin<\/code> section of <code>pom.xml<\/code>:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&lt;annotationProcessorArg>micronaut.openapi.views.spec=rapidoc.enabled=true,swagger-ui.enabled=true,swagger-ui.theme=flattop&lt;\/annotationProcessorArg><\/code><\/pre>\n\n\n\n<p>And now re-run the server with:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>JAVA_HOME=$(\/usr\/libexec\/java_home -v 11)\n.\/mvnw clean mn:run<\/code><\/pre>\n\n\n\n<p>Finally, Swagger UI is available at: <a href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/swagger-ui\">http:\/\/localhost:8080\/swagger-ui<\/a>. If you have any issues, you can check this <a href=\"https:\/\/github.com\/uroshekic\/micronaut-openapi-example\/commits\/master\">demo repository<\/a> on GitHub.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>I was playing around with Micronaut framework 2.0 which was released a couple of days ago (June 26th) for a personal project, a web service with a REST API. I wanted to use Swagger UI, but Micronaut\u2019s documentation does not cover how to set it up with Maven and Kotlin. It went something like this. [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[10],"tags":[3,2],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"","_links":{"self":[{"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8000\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/27"}],"collection":[{"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8000\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8000\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8000\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8000\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=27"}],"version-history":[{"count":12,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8000\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/27\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":55,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8000\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/27\/revisions\/55"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8000\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=27"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8000\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=27"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8000\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=27"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}